17:55.888 --> 17:57.416
It's exhausting, right?

17:57.547 --> 17:59.181
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

17:59.394 --> 18:00.727
And they're not even tipping.

18:00.792 --> 18:02.392
Oh, the clients tip us
at the end.

18:02.483 --> 18:03.642
Oh, yeah? How well?

18:03.749 --> 18:06.417
Okay. Drunk dudes paying
with expense accounts

18:06.560 --> 18:07.826
tend to be generous.

18:07.891 --> 18:09.017
So what about the weddings?

18:09.088 --> 18:10.400
You want 'em rich.

18:10.462 --> 18:12.361
But not too rich,
because if they're too rich,

18:12.431 --> 18:15.836
they never had to work for it,
tips are crap.

18:16.002 --> 18:17.760
How do you, uh, tell who's rich

18:17.853 --> 18:19.213
when you're choosing
your shifts?

18:19.275 --> 18:22.728
Go online, search the date,
the boat.

18:23.096 --> 18:25.119
You can figure out
who the rich clients are.

18:25.273 --> 18:26.433
Smart girl.

18:26.458 --> 18:27.504
Well...

18:29.572 --> 18:33.119
So why can't these
be traced?

18:33.744 --> 18:36.400
They're made of compressed
copper powder

18:36.478 --> 18:41.189
and they just crumble on impact.

18:41.963 --> 18:43.787
Now seat it.

18:51.134 --> 18:56.070
I had to get rid of Javi, j,
for you,

18:56.369 --> 19:00.408
because he broke into our home
and hurt you.

19:01.151 --> 19:03.267
And because you wanted me to.

19:03.576 --> 19:07.463
